commit 6a9bb5b13018fddb415d818252fde2b8a65c1c6c
Author: cevr <seeve.c@gmail.com>
Date:   Wed Jun 17 11:16:49 2026 -0400

    feat(cms)(list-edit): retire the index assumption — identity-keyed merge/navigation

    Sub-commit 2.4 (ADR 0006). The id-keyed structural edit (2.2/2.3) is now the
    ONLY way lists move; this deletes the index assumption's remaining homes and
    migrates every caller to address list items + conferences by stable identity
    (`<id>` / `<slug>`), never by array position.

    Deletions (migrate-callers-then-delete):
    - `deepMerge`'s array-by-index branch → identity-keyed merge: an object override
      (`{ <id>: partial }` / `{ "/2024": partial }`) onto an array base matches each
      key against the item whose `id`/`slug` equals it; an edit can never land on the
      wrong item after a list grew/shrank.
    - `setPath`'s numeric array-construction + `setAtPath`'s list-index navigation →
      `setByIdentity`: the override is a pure object tree, and the image-upload
      rewrite resolves array segments by identity (creating only missing OBJECT keys,
      never fabricating array items).
    - the view's positional `speakers.${si}` / `team.${ti}` field-name templates →
      `fieldName(listPath, item.id, leaf)`; conferences keyed by `slug`.

    `applyListEdit`'s path navigation (`updateListAtPath`) is unified to the same
    identity resolution, since the view now hands `applyListOps` slug-keyed
    conference paths. Callers migrated: the admin route, the editDocument
    equivalence corpus, applyImageUpload, the list-op e2e, and the unit tests.
    Adds position-independence tests (an edit lands on its id after a reorder).

    Gate green: typecheck, lint, build, 231 tests.

